{
  "id": "tpl-five-phase-debate",
  "name": "5-Phase Debate (Extended Roles)",
  "description": "A comprehensive 5-phase debate workflow with 15 specialized roles and a meta-orchestrator.\n\nPhase 1 — Problem Framing: Analyst, Creative Thinker, Socratic Questioner\nPhase 2 — Position Building: Strategist, Expert Reviewer, Steel-manner\nPhase 3 — Stress Testing: Devil's Advocate, Fact Checker, Troll (bad faith, labeled)\nPhase 4 — Integration: Mediator, Ethicist, Synthesizer\nPhase 5 — Closure: Moderator, Critic, Optimizer\n\nKey design choice: Troll and Devil's Advocate are separate roles — Troll tests rhetorical robustness (bad faith, labeled); Devil's Advocate tests logical robustness (good faith). Conflating them weakens both signals.\n\nThe Orchestrator meta-agent reads debate state and decides which role speaks next, preventing role-stacking fatigue and keeping the debate dynamic.",
  "category": "system",
  "tags": [
    "debate",
    "5-phase",
    "extended",
    "multi-agent",
    "orchestrator",
    "troll",
    "devils-advocate",
    "stress-testing",
    "structured"
  ],
